description: Britains Lost Masterpieces: Collection 1 History Documentary hosted by Bendor Grosvenor and Jacky Klein and Emma Dabiri, published by BBC in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/d/d8/Britains-Lost-Masterpieces-Collection-1-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Britain's Lost Masterpieces: Collection 1 Historian and art dealer Dr Bendor Grosvenor, art historian Jacky Klein and Emma Dabiri celebrate the UK's local art treasures as they track down lost and hidden paintings from local museums and galleries. This Collection is made up of 3 episodes from Series 1, 4 episodes from Series 2 2) Aberdeenshire Haddo House is one of Britain's most northerly stately homes. Tucked away in the wilds of Aberdeenshire, it has been home to prime ministers and earls - but is it also home to some of Scotland's greatest lost paintings? Nearby, in the storerooms of the Montrose Museum lies a mystery painting with a giant hole in it.
